input: Country: Spain. Purchaser Name: PARETS DEL VALLÈS COUNCIL. Summary: Drafting of the Basic Project for the Reform of the Works of the Future Facilities of the Social Rights Service of the Parets Del Vallès City Council.. Description: Description of the service: The object of the contract is the procurement promoted by the Urban Planning area, consisting of the drafting of the basic project for the reform of the works of the future installations of the Social Rights service of the City Council of Parets del Vallès, located in the municipal building on carrer de la Volta, 2 Building H2 2nd floor, including the entirety of this first floor, when sizing the facilities and the functionality of this floor. It will include the drafting of the basic project and health and safety study. Basic project: it is the work phase in which the general characteristics of the work are precisely defined through the adoption and justification of the concrete solutions. This document must justify the constructive, structural and installation solutions of a general type as well as a general definition of the finishing materials. At the same time you will have to consider the generic geometric and architectural definition (with scale plans) and an estimate overall budget. You must also justify, at the basic project level, the energy certification of the project. Its content must be sufficient to apply for the corresponding municipal building license and other authorizations administrative. Safety and health study: Drafting of the corresponding safety and health study to obtain the corresponding license.. Published Date: 2025-12-26. Closing Date: 2026-01-10. Competition: ICB. Financier Name: Self Financed

output.Purchaser_Name: PARETS DEL VALLÈS COUNCIL

Airport Section - Pozo Negro Crossing. Fuerteventura Island. Description: The object of the contract will be the execution of the work "PUERTO DEL ROSARIO - MORRO JABLE ROAD. SECTION: AIRPORT - CRUCE DEPOZO NEGRO. FUERTEVENTURA ISLAND", specifically, the execution of a road with a length of 16,775 meters and a classification highway with a design speed of 120 km/h and a level of service C, which is located in the central-eastern region of the Island of Fuerteventura, its route running through the Municipalities of Puerto del Rosario and Antigua, in a North-South direction along the interior, bypassing the towns of Matorral and Castillo until a little before the Llanos de Cancela where it meets the current FV-2 and from there it runs in an East - West direction until reaching the current Pozo Negro Crossing. It starts in the around the Airport, where it connects with the current Puerto del Rosario-Airport highway (FV-2), practically once the Río Cabras Ravine has been cleared, ending at the existing intersection of Antigua (intersection of the FV-2 with the FV-50 heading to Antigua and Valles de Ortega), better known as "the Pozo Negro crossing". The general cross section of the corridor is made up of a 37.00 meter wide platform distributed in: four (4) lanes of 3.50 meters (two in each direction); two (2) shoulders exteriors of 2.50 meters; two (2) 1.00 meter interior shoulders; four (4) berms of 1.00 meters and a median of twelve (12) meters. To resolve the interconnections of the projected road with the rest of the road.... Published Date: 2025-12-24. Closing Date: 2026-02-05. Competition: ICB. Financier Name: Self Financed

Summary: The Object of the Contract Consists of the Execution of the Expansion Works of the Existing Warehouse Intended for the Treatment of Bulky Waste Within the Cervillian Waste Recovery Complex.... Description: The object of the contract consists of the execution of the expansion works of the existing warehouse intended for the treatment of bulky waste within the Cervillian waste recovery complex... The scope of the contract includes the material execution complete of the works necessary for the expansion of the bulky waste warehouse, including all the constructive, structural and functional actions required for its correct integration into the existing recovery complex and for its installation in operation in accordance with the applicable technical, environmental and safety regulations. The works will be carried out strictly subject to the technical project that is an integral part of the contract, which includes descriptive and constructive memory, compliance with the Technical Building Code and other sector regulations, waste management study, quality control, health and safety study, plans, technical specifications, measurements and budget. The contractual object It also includes all the operations necessary for the correct execution and completion of the work, so that the installation is fully operational, without requiring additional payment for work essential to achieve said result. end. The purpose of the contract consists of the execution of the expansion works of the existing warehouse intended for the treatment of bulky waste within the Cervera del Maestre waste recovery complex, promoted by the Consortium of C1 waste from the Valencian Community. The Polytechnic University of Valencia has among its purposes training, research and the generation of knowledge, with the aim of promoting the comprehensive development of society and contributing to its technological, economic and cultural progress. It currently has three university campuses located in Valencia, Gandía and Alcoy, with around 40,000 daily users in its facilities, 120 buildings and more than 5,500 parking spaces available. The Institute of Molecular and Cellular Biology of Plants (IBMCP) is a university institute of joint research from the Polytechnic University of Valencia (UPV) and the Higher Council for Scientific Research (CSIC). To guarantee adequate safety conditions, both for people and property, it is necessary to have a surveillance and security service. Phase V" Project. Description: Description of the service: The object of the project "Restoration of the Castle of Els Garidells. Phase V" is the adaptation and putting into use, by the administration, of a space of the castle of Els Garidells excavated using archaeological methods in the course of the previous restoration phases. This area corresponds to the basement of the Torre del Homenaje. The use that the conditioned space will house will be a museum and dissemination of the history of the Garidells castle, as well as the municipality, its inhabitants and their environment. To this end, the adaptation of the circulation level is proposed, the functional recovery of the interior stairs, the covering of these to prevent water access through the stairwell and the waterproofing of the floor. the ground floor to avoid leaks to the basement. The purpose of the works intended with the project is the development of the proposal for actions inside the castle to adapt the basement space to a new use as an area museum-informative, while the necessary conservation and restoration work is proposed to clean up and consolidate the vertical walls of said space.. Published Date: 2025-12-23. Closing Date: 2026-01-12. Competition: ICB. Financier Name: Self Financed

output.Purchaser_Name: COUNCIL OF THE GARIDELLS

Phase V" is the adaptation and putting into use, by the administration, of a space of the castle of Els Garidells excavated using archaeological methods in the course of the previous restoration phases. This area corresponds to the basement of the Torre del Homenaje. The use that the conditioned space will house will be a museum and dissemination of the history of the Garidells castle, as well as the municipality, its inhabitants and their environment. To this end, the adaptation of the circulation level is proposed, the functional recovery of the interior stairs, the covering of these to prevent water access through the stairwell and the waterproofing of the floor. the ground floor to avoid leaks to the basement. The purpose of the works intended with the project is the development of the proposal for actions inside the castle to adapt the basement space to a new use as an area museum-informative, while the necessary conservation and restoration work is proposed to clean up and consolidate the vertical walls of said space.

input: Country: Spain. Purchaser Name: TOWN CITY OF VIDRÁ. Summary: Construction of a Square in Front of the Consistorial House of Vidrà. Description: Description of the service: The square in front of the Casa de la Vila de Vidrà is widened with the construction of a wall of approximately 5m. height and the subsequent formation of a slab on which to organize the newly created public space, linking with the current one. This action entails the construction of an intermediate structure made up of pillars and girders in order to reduce the light in the span. The works also foresee the reinforcement of the current wall, which is double with a twinned wall and also the forecast of the foundations of a future building destined for a civic center with the construction of two structural walls that complement the rest of the structure.. The Port Authority of Tarragona calls for a tender public in order to select the best offer for the subsequent processing and granting of an administrative concession for the construction and operation of a multipurpose terminal open to general use attached to the Andalusia dock, in the Port of Tarragona, with an intermodal vocation and railway integration, for this purpose, it is possible to include in the same title the concession and operation of the annexed railway terminal of La Boella. input: Country: Spain. Purchaser Name: GENERAL DIRECTORATE OF WATER. Summary: Contracting of Works to Adapt to the Bco Flood Risk. Barxeta. Phase Ii.. Description: The actions planned in the construction project “ADAPTATION TO THE FLOOD RISK OF THE BARXETA CANYON. PHASE II” is declared of General Interest, as it is included in the list of investments of the Annex II of the National Hydrological Plan, approved by Law 10/2001, of July 5, with the name “Conditioning of the Júcar river between Carcaixent and the A-7 highway.” Actions included in the program measures of the Flood Risk Management Plan for the Hydrographic Demarcation of the Júcar. A reinforced concrete protection wall is projected, leading the waters towards an mouth where has planned a low water channel in order to divert the environmental flow of the Barxeta to the low drainage work the CV-41, equipped with a gate. The rest of the flow is channeled through the new channel of the Barxeta ravine, Its renaturalization is planned by widening the existing channel and covering the slopes with topsoil and breakwater, until the junction with the Camí de l'Horta, which resolves through a typology structure frame. The pass provides continuity to the existing crossing over the Barxeta and allows access to the center of Carcaixent and the path located on the left bank of the old Barxeta riverbed. Next, is projected in the following A relief channel runs downstream until it connects with phase I, which finally leads the waters to the Júcar River. Financed by FEDER Funds Spain's Pluriregional Operational Program 2.... Published Date: 2025-12-19. Closing Date: 2026-02-10. Competition: ICB. Financier Name: Self Financed

HE plans the construction of the final section of the relief channel of the Barxeta ravine, about 800 meters long, from the junction of the current Barxeta with the Primer de Benivaire road, to its mouth in the Júcar river, giving continuity to the works collected in Phase II. In order to make the flows of the Júcar river and ravine independent Barxeta of the urban center of Carcaixent, a protection area is projected located to the north of the variant and before of the overpass over the railway, using to This is land from the excavation of the new riverbed. relief. It is also planned to carry out different environmental integration works, as well as the replacement of the affected services and roads, highlighting the main road replacements, that corresponding to the road CV-5440 (replaced by a service road on the left bank of the channel), and that relating to the Alborgí road, which It will cross the new channel on 5 prefabricated frames....
